---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CATALOG } from '../lib/catalog';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import PageNextActions from '../components/PageNextActions.astro';

const schema = {
	'@context': 'https://schema.org',
	'@type': 'Organization',
	name: '3D3D',
	description: 'Founder-operated specialty fabrication for marine, restoration, and route-based field deployment.',
	url: 'https://3d3d.ca',
	email: 'info@3d3d.ca',
	founder: { '@type': 'Person', name: 'Ken' },
	areaServed: ['Worldwide', 'Caribbean', 'Coastal United States', 'Europe'],
};

const stats = [
	{ value: `${CATALOG.length}`, label: 'Products' },
	{ value: '5', label: 'Materials' },
	{ value: '24-48h', label: 'Turnaround' },
	{ value: '2', label: 'Events' },
];
const aboutGallery = [
  {
    src: '/media/workshop/printed-cup-shell.jpg',
    alt: '3D printed cup shell part on a printer bed',
    title: 'Functional print work',
  },
  {
    src: '/media/workshop/machine-parts-flatlay.jpg',
    alt: 'Black machine parts and rings laid out on a workbench',
    title: 'Small-batch production parts',
  },
  {
    src: '/media/workshop/blue-prototype-part.jpg',
    alt: 'Blue 3D printed prototype part held in front of a monitor',
    title: 'Prototype iterations',
  },
  {
    src: '/media/workshop/printer-action-cf.jpg',
    alt: 'FDM machine printing carbon fiber filament',
    title: 'High-temp capable fleet',
  },
  {
    src: '/media/workshop/printer-bed-benchy.jpg',
    alt: 'Multiple test benchies on a build plate',
    title: 'Calibration and tuning',
  },
  {
    src: '/media/workshop/rv-lab-03.jpg',
    alt: 'Workshop desk setup with monitors and tools',
    title: 'The command center',
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout title="About | 3D3D" description="Founder-operated specialty fabrication. Ken's story, from early open-source builds to boats, motorsport, route support, and field deployment." schema={schema} activePath="/about">

<div class="pt-8 pb-12">
<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
<Breadcrumbs items={[{label: 'Home', href: '/'}, {label: 'About'}]} />
<div class="about-hero surface-panel">
<div class="about-hero__background" aria-hidden="true"></div>
<div class="about-hero__content">
<p class="font-display text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">About</p>
<h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mt-2 mb-6 scroll-in" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">About 3D3D</h1>

<div class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed scroll-in-fade scroll-delay-1" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
<p>
Seventy-five knots sustained. Ninety-knot gusts. Four days of continuous survival in a bomb cyclone off the East Coast. There were only two of us on the sailboat, it was my first time at sea, and at the worst of it, we assessed whether pulling the EPIRB was survivable. We chose to endure without it. When it broke, we sailed another nine days to Antigua, detouring three hundred miles around Bermuda to dodge a second system. I went from crawling on the deck in terror to standing solo night watches.
</p>
<p>
That was my introduction to the ocean.
</p>
<p>
<strong>I know what breaks, because I have been there when it did.</strong>
</p>
<p>
My background is not in software, and it is not in rapid prototyping. It is in keeping complex machinery alive when failure has severe consequences. Since that first passage, I have sailed over 20,000 nautical miles. I have crossed the North Atlantic in eleven days aboard a stripped-down Volvo 60. I have seen thirty-metre waves, and I have fallen off them in a 60-foot Kevlar hull. I have achieved twenty-six knots at the helm on a surf run. I spent seven months living and working aboard a 1946 Dutch-built 42-foot ketch, and I have stood watch alongside some of the best offshore sailors in the world. They trusted me when the weather turned foul.
</p>
<p>
Before the ocean, I spent ten years as a professional mechanic. I have restored AMC AMXs, Roadrunners, Dodge Polaras, and GTOs. I know what it means to hunt for a part last manufactured in 1979, and I know how to fabricate it when the supply chain is dead.
</p>
<p>
Trust is the only currency that matters in this work. A client in Thailand handed me a $50,000 credit card to fund a month-long project. I executed the work and returned the card without spending a dollar over what was strictly required. When I tell you what a job takes, that is exactly what it takes.
</p>
<p>
The 3D printer is not my product. It is simply the most capable item in a toolkit built over two decades, allowing us to bypass dead supply chains and put a finished part in your hands the same day.
</p>

<div class="mt-8 p-6 rounded-lg bg-teal-50/50 border border-teal-100">
<h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold mb-3" style="color: var(--color-teal-primary);">Not a Print Shop. A Cooperative.</h3>
<p class="text-sm">
3D3D is not a middleman slicing service. It is a distributed manufacturing cooperative. We maintain a fleet of local operators equipped with vetted machines. 
We operate transparently—makers keep 75% of order value, we build open-source tools to route the jobs securely, and we push code to the public on <a href="https://github.com/3d3dcanada" target="_blank" class="font-semibold text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-900">GitHub</a>.
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mt-12">
{stats.map((stat) => (
<div class="text-center p-4 rounded-xl" style="background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);">
<span class="block font-display text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-teal-primary);">{stat.value}</span>
<span class="font-display text-[9px] uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">{stat.label}</span>
</div>
))}
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="about-gallery">
{aboutGallery.map((item) => (
<figure class="surface-panel about-gallery__card">
<img src={item.src} alt={item.alt} loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
<figcaption>
<strong>{item.title}</strong>
</figcaption>
</figure>
))}
</div>

{/* How it works */}
<div class="mt-16">
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mb-6 scroll-in" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">How It Works</h2>
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
{[
{ step: '01', title: 'Tell me about your event or project', desc: 'Describe what you need: hard-to-find parts for a boat, props for a race, or custom pieces for a community build.' },
{ step: '02', title: 'I show up with printers and cameras', desc: 'I bring the equipment on-site, print parts in real time, and document the process on video.' },
{ step: '03', title: 'You get parts, content, and the experience', desc: 'Walk away with functional printed parts, video content of the build, and a story worth sharing.' },
].map((item) => (
<div class="p-5 rounded-xl" style="background: var(--color-surface-card); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);">
<span class="font-display text-3xl font-bold opacity-40" style="color: var(--color-teal-primary);">{item.step}</span>
<h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold mt-2 mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">{item.title}</h3>
<p class="text-xs leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">{item.desc}</p>
</div>
))}
</div>
</div>

      {/* The Open Source Cooperative */}
      <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/5" style="border-top-color: var(--color-border-subtle);">
        <p class="font-display text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2" style="color: var(--color-teal-primary);">The Model</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold mb-6 scroll-in" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">An Open Source Cooperative</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 scroll-in-fade">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
              3D3D is not a traditional corporation. It operates as an open-source manufacturing cooperative. The designs, the code, the operational blueprints, and the failures are all shared. We build tools so that others can build them too, decentralized and locally.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
              This model ensures that when supply chains fail, you aren't waiting on a shipment from across the world. You ping the network, download the tested file, and a local node builds it. That is the reality we are constructing.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
              <a href="https://github.com/3d3dcanada" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded" style="background: var(--color-surface-card); color: var(--color-text-primary); border: 2px solid var(--color-text-primary); transition: all 0.2s;">
                GitHub Repo →
              </a>
              <a href="https://printables.com/@KTK3D_3050116" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded" style="background: var(--color-surface-card); color: var(--color-text-primary); border: 2px solid var(--color-text-primary); transition: all 0.2s;">
                Printables →
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 rounded-xl" style="background: var(--color-surface-card); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);">
            <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">The Old Girl</h3>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
              A sister project demonstrating the model. An open-source FDM machine restored and handed over to the community. Print queue, donations, livestream. A physical printer that belongs to the internet.
            </p>
            <a href="https://oldgirl.3d3d.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-display text-xs uppercase tracking-wider hover:underline block mt-4" style="color: var(--color-teal-primary);">
              Visit the node →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <PageNextActions actions={[
        {label: 'Get a Quote', href: '/quote', description: 'Start a project with an operator who shows up.', accent: 'teal'},
        {label: 'Browse the Shop', href: '/shop', description: 'Ready-made prints and cooperative goods.', accent: 'orange'},
        {label: 'Join the Network', href: '/opportunities', description: 'Work with us as a maker or specialist.', accent: 'magenta'},
      ]} />
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    position: relative;
    isolation: isolate;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .about-hero__background {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(244, 251, 251, 0.92), rgba(255, 245, 250, 0.78)),
      url('/media/backgrounds/about-print-lab.jpg') center / cover no-repeat;
    opacity: 0.82;
  }

  .about-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .about-gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
  }

  .about-gallery__card {
    padding: 0.85rem;
  }

  .about-gallery__card img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .about-gallery__card figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
  }

  .about-gallery__card strong {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
